# Secrets & Environment Variables

> Reference manually with `@secrets-and-env`. Full registry: `docs/CURSOR_HANDOVER.md` §2. **No secret values in this file or in git.**

## GitHub Actions secrets (names + purpose)

| Secret | Purpose |
| ------ | ------- |
| `GOLDPRICEZ_API_KEY` | Gold price API key (api.goldpricez.com) — used by price workflows |
| `CONSUMER_KEY` | X/Twitter OAuth 1.0a API Key (hourly posting) |
| `CONSUMER_SECRET` | X/Twitter OAuth 1.0a API Secret |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN` | X/Twitter Access Token (Read+Write) |
| `ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET` | X/Twitter Access Token Secret |
| `SUPABASE_URL` | Supabase project URL |
| `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` | Service-role key (server-side only; bypasses RLS) |
| `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` | Telegram Bot API — alerts |
| `TELEGRAM_CHANNEL_ID` | Telegram channel/group ID |
| `DISCORD_WEBHOOK_URL` | Discord webhook — alerts |
| `SUPABASE_MCP_TOKEN` | Legacy MCP bearer (deprecated in workflows — prefer local `SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`) |

Production fetch workflow also references provider keys via secrets (see `gold-price-fetch.yml`): `GOLD_API_COM_KEY`, `TWELVEDATA_API_KEY`, `TWELVEDATA_SYMBOL`, `FMP_API_KEY`, `FMP_SYMBOL`, and `GOLDPRICEZ_API_KEY`.

### X/Twitter naming quirk

Repository secrets are **`CONSUMER_*` / `ACCESS_*`** (no `TWITTER_` prefix). Workflow env uses `TWITTER_API_KEY`, `TWITTER_API_SECRET`, `TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN`, `TWITTER_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET`.

## Local `.env` (copy from `.env.example`)

### Required for `npm start` / `npm test`

| Variable | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| `JWT_SECRET` | Signs JWT admin tokens (32+ chars) — **required** |
| `ADMIN_PASSWORD` | Admin panel password — **required** |

### Optional admin

| Variable | Purpose |
| -------- | ------- |
| `ADMIN_ACCESS_PIN` | 6+ digit PIN gate; disabled when unset |

### Gold providers (representative)

| Variable | Purpose | Default (from `.env.example`) |
| -------- | ------- | ------------------------------- |
| `GOLD_PROVIDER_ORDER` | Comma-separated provider priority | `metal_sentinel,finnhub_oanda,fmp_gcusd,goldapi_io,twelvedata_xauusd,goldpricez` |
| `AED_PEG` | USD→AED rate | `3.6725` |
| `MAX_GOLD_FRESHNESS_SECONDS` | Max age before stale | `900` |
| `MIN_VALID_XAU_USD` / `MAX_VALID_XAU_USD` | Sanity bounds | `500` / `10000` |
| `GOLDPRICEZ_ENABLED` / `GOLDPRICEZ_API_KEY` | GoldPriceZ provider | enabled / — |
| `METAL_SENTINEL_*`, `FINNHUB_*`, `FMP_*`, `GOLDAPI_IO_*`, `TWELVEDATA_*`, `GOLD_API_COM_*` | Optional provider toggles + API keys | mostly disabled |

